 "transcript": [
  {
   "start": 0.18,
   "end": 6.4,
   "text": "Desert, sweep in a broad arc from the Grand Canyon into western New Mexico."
  },
  {
   "start": 7.68,
   "end": 14.52,
   "text": "Petrified Forest National Park occupies a relatively small but important part of this"
  },
  {
   "start": 14.52,
   "end": 15.62,
   "text": "Colorful landscape."
  },
  {
   "start": 17.51,
   "end": 24.97,
   "text": "What separates these lands from all others is petrified wood, bejeweled with quartz"
  },
  {
   "start": 24.97,
   "end": 30.69,
   "text": "Crystals, agate, jasper, amethyst, and other semi-precious gems."
  },
  {
   "start": 30.69,
   "end": 36.44,
   "text": "Petrified wood is not rare."
  },
  {
   "start": 36.98,
   "end": 41.52,
   "text": "It can be found in all 50 states and in many countries throughout the world."
  },
  {
   "start": 42.26,
   "end": 47.48,
   "text": "But nowhere else on earth is there a place like the petrified forest."
  },
  {
   "start": 48.28,
   "end": 55.46,
   "text": "Nowhere else is there such a great collection of exposed, colorful fossil trees."
  },
  {
   "start": 55.46,
   "end": 68.42,
   "text": "Written 25 million years ago, in a time we call the Triassic period, the continents of"
  },
  {
   "start": 68.42,
   "end": 71.04,
   "text": "The world formed a single landmass."
  },
  {
   "start": 71.8,
   "end": 77.12,
   "text": "Arizona was part of a tropical jungle near the location of present-day Panama."
  },
  {
   "start": 81.11,
   "end": 88.19,
   "text": "Many millions of years ago, a rampaging torrent ripped trees from their tenuous hold along"
  },
  {
   "start": 88.19,
   "end": 89.59,
   "text": "An ancient riverbank."
  },
  {
   "start": 89.59,
   "end": 97.09,
   "text": "The trees were to begin a journey that would take them not only downstream, but through time."
  },
  {
   "start": 98.25,
   "end": 105.87,
   "text": "Trees became entangled and roots and limbs snapped as the giant logs tumbled across the river"
  },
  {
   "start": 105.87,
   "end": 106.25,
   "text": "Bottom."
  },
  {
   "start": 107.21,
   "end": 110.21,
   "text": "Reaching the floodplain, their journey slowed."
  },
  {
   "start": 110.95,
   "end": 114.03,
   "text": "The logs became mired in swamplands."
  },
  {
   "start": 115.03,
   "end": 117.67,
   "text": "Waterlogged, they sank to the bottom."
  },
  {
   "start": 117.67,
   "end": 127.78,
   "text": "The trees were quickly covered by a mixture of sand, silt, and highly absorbent ash, spewed"
  },
  {
   "start": 127.78,
   "end": 129.44,
   "text": "From volcanic eruptions."
  },
  {
   "start": 130.56,
   "end": 133.8,
   "text": "The ash was rich with a mineral called silica."
  },
  {
   "start": 134.7,
   "end": 139.78,
   "text": "The logs were sealed from the ravages of time and decay."
  },
  {
   "start": 145.6,
   "end": 149.22,
   "text": "The silica-rich water seeped deep into the pores of the wood."
  },
  {
   "start": 149.22,
   "end": 156.74,
   "text": "Slowly, the silica began to react chemically to the wood, displacing the cellulose."
  },
  {
   "start": 156.74,
   "end": 164.24,
   "text": "The reaction caused microscopic quartz crystals to grow within the pores, replacing the wood"
  },
  {
   "start": 164.24,
   "end": 167.46,
   "text": "Cell by cell with solid rock."
  },
  {
   "start": 169.46,
   "end": 176.24,
   "text": "Decayed organic matter and minerals like iron and manganese stained the crystals, creating"
  },
  {
   "start": 176.24,
   "end": 177.76,
   "text": "A kaleidoscope of colors."
  },
  {
   "start": 177.76,
   "end": 186.74,
   "text": "Today, the minerals also stain the clays of the chimney formation, the layers of rock"
  },
  {
   "start": 186.74,
   "end": 189.12,
   "text": "That hold the petrified forest."
  },
  {
   "start": 189.36,
   "end": 200.03,
   "text": "Millions of years, the logs lay buried in the chimney formation, buried in a clay tomb beneath"
  },
  {
   "start": 200.03,
   "end": 209.95,
   "text": "Hundreds, perhaps thousands of feet of sand, slowly, pressures deep within the earth's crust, began"
  },
  {
   "start": 209.95,
   "end": 216.83,
   "text": "Pushing the Colorado Plateau upward, countered by the forces of erosion cutting downwards."
  },
  {
   "start": 216.83,
   "end": 227.61,
   "text": "It is here, now, after millions of years, that these opposing forces finally meet to reveal"
  },
  {
   "start": 227.61,
   "end": 229.79,
   "text": "The petrified forests."
  },
  {
   "start": 229.79,
   "end": 241.54,
   "text": "The ancient Chinle swamps of Triassic times were subtropical, lush, with varied shades of green."
  },
  {
   "start": 242.64,
   "end": 248.92,
   "text": "The smell of stagnant water, mixed with rotting vegetation, permeated the humid air."
  },
  {
   "start": 248.92,
   "end": 256.2,
   "text": "Many of the plants and trees would be recognizable, but only a few of the animals would"
  },
  {
   "start": 256.2,
   "end": 258.54,
   "text": "Resemble anything existing today."
  },
  {
   "start": 258.54,
   "end": 266.59,
   "text": "A vicious carnivore once stalked this prehistoric forest."
  },
  {
   "start": 267.67,
   "end": 271.51,
   "text": "It stood upright, balanced by its long tail."
  },
  {
   "start": 273.23,
   "end": 280.35,
   "text": "In Coelophysis, by the scientists that discovered the fossilized remains, it measured about four"
  },
  {
   "start": 280.35,
   "end": 283.09,
   "text": "Feet high and probably hunted in packs."
  },
  {
   "start": 283.09,
   "end": 291.71,
   "text": "The largest plant-eaters of the time were the Placereus digus, they were reptiles."
  },
  {
   "start": 291.71,
   "end": 312.5,
   "text": "The Painted Desert, red, red rock here in Navajo country."
  },
  {
   "start": 312.5,
   "end": 321.13,
   "text": "You can find fossils."
  },
  {
